The paper discusses organizational science and the need to investigate agility at multiple levels of analysis, including the macro (organizational), meso (team), and micro (individual) levels. This suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as well as cybernetics (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG) for developing validated measurements. Additionally, the paper's emphasis on providing actionable guidelines for practitioners suggests a focus on social and information sciences (cs.SI).
